  "Notes": [
    {
      "Text": "libxslt security update",
      "Title": "Synopsis",
      "Type": "General"
    },
    {
      "Text": "An update for libxslt is now available for openEuler-24.03-LTS-SP2",
      "Title": "Summary",
      "Type": "General"
    },
    {
      "Text": "Libxslt is the XSLT C library developed for the GNOME project\n\nSecurity Fix(es):\n\nA flaw was found in the exsltFuncResultComp() function of libxslt, which handles EXSLT \u003cfunc:result\u003e elements during stylesheet parsing. Due to improper type handling, the function may treat an XML document node as a regular XML element node, resulting in a type confusion. This can cause unexpected memory reads and potential crashes. While difficult to exploit, the flaw could lead to application instability or denial of service.(CVE-2025-11731)",
      "Title": "Description",
      "Type": "General"
    },
    {
      "Text": "An update for libxslt is now available for openEuler-24.03-LTS-SP2.\n\nopenEuler Security has rated this update as having a security impact of low. A Common Vunlnerability Scoring System(CVSS)base score,which gives a detailed severity rating, is available for each vulnerability from the CVElink(s) in the References section.",
      "Title": "Topic",
      "Type": "General"
    },
    {
      "Text": "Low",
      "Title": "Severity",
      "Type": "General"
    },
    {
      "Text": "libxslt",
      "Title": "Affected Component",
      "Type": "General"
    }
  ],
